<h1>@HI{{made}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}}<strong>@HI{{made}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{made}}</strong> is indicates a time limit for an action: "until".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KT{{depa-to}}ha,@KJ{{soil^weekday^day}}to@KJ{{day^weekday^day}}ha8@KJ{{time}}<strong>made</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This department store is open until 8 on Saturdays and Sundays.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{made}}</strong> can indicate the place to which an action extends.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kokokara@KJ{{capital^metropolis}}<strong>made</strong>@KJ{{what^time^interval}}kakarimasuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      How long does it take to get from here to Kyoto?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{made}}</strong> can indicate the degree of a condition by citing an example.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{child^submit}}dakedenaku@KJ{{large^person}}<strong>made</strong>,sono@KT{{ge-mu}}wo@KJ{{music}}shinda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Not only children but even adults enjoyed that game.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{made}}</strong> can indicate an extreme condition.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{adjusted^wisteria}}sanha,ano@KJ{{male}}no@KJ{{person}}to@KJ{{tie^marriage}}dekinakereba@KJ{{death}}nouto
      <strong>made</strong>@KJ{{think}}itsumetasoudesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Saito was apparently even contemplating suicide if she were unable to marry the man.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
When X refers to a duration of time, then "X <strong>@HI{{made}}</strong>" means "up to and including X" rather than "until X"
(the latter usually excludes X).

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{come^week}}no@KJ{{month^weekday^day}}<strong>made</strong>@KJ{{rest}}mimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'll be away up to and including next Monday.
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      <em>I'll be away until next Tuesday.</em>
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

